---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Demonstrations"
  subtitle="PROTEUS resolves the coupled interior-atmosphere evolution of rocky planets from a molten beginning."
  description="Demonstration of the PROTEUS framework simulating magma ocean solidification and atmosphere formation for early Earth."
  image="/assets/img/og-default.jpg"
>
  <!-- Earth scenario -->
<h2 class="section-label">Early Earth</h2>

<div class="scenario-pane">
  <div class="scenario-top">
    <div class="scenario-video-col">
      <video autoplay="" muted="" playsinline="" loop="" controls="">
        <source src="/assets/demos/earth/video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
    </div>
    <div class="scenario-info-col">
      <div class="at-a-glance">
        <h3>At a glance</h3>
        <table>
          <tr><td>Mass</td><td>1 M<sub>Earth</sub></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Orbit</td><td>1 AU (Sun)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Volatiles</td><td>1 Earth ocean H<sub>2</sub>O</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Redox</td><td>IW+4</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Interior</td><td>SPIDER (magma ocean dynamics)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Atmosphere</td><td>AGNI (radiative-convective)</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="outcome">
          <strong>Outcome:</strong> Full mantle solidification within ~2 Myr
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="result-gallery">
    <div class="result-card">
      <img class="plot-dark" src="/assets/demos/earth/thermal-dark.png" alt="Earth thermal evolution" loading="lazy" />
      <img class="plot-light" src="/assets/demos/earth/thermal-light.png" alt="Earth thermal evolution" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="result-label">Thermal evolution</div>
    </div>
    <div class="result-card">
      <img class="plot-dark" src="/assets/demos/earth/volatiles-dark.png" alt="Earth volatile inventory" loading="lazy" />
      <img class="plot-light" src="/assets/demos/earth/volatiles-light.png" alt="Earth volatile inventory" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="result-label">Volatile inventory</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <details class="demo-detail" open="">
    <summary>Detailed interpretation</summary>
    <div class="detail-body">
      <p>Starting from a fully molten mantle after a giant impact, PROTEUS tracks how Earth's magma ocean solidifies and volatiles outgas to form a thick steam atmosphere.</p>
      <p>The simulation begins with a high mantle entropy (2900 J/K/kg) representing the aftermath of the Moon-forming impact. As the magma ocean cools, dissolved volatiles partition into the atmosphere following thermochemical equilibrium (CALLIOPE). The atmosphere becomes dominated by H<sub>2</sub>O, CO<sub>2</sub>, and sulfur species.</p>
      <p>The surface cools from ~3400 K to ~1400 K within the first ~2 million years, with the last few percent of deep-mantle melt persisting through rheological transitions. By the end of solidification the atmosphere has grown to ~290 bar (~210 bar H<sub>2</sub>O, ~50 bar CO<sub>2</sub>, plus N<sub>2</sub>, H<sub>2</sub>S, and SO<sub>2</sub>). This thick steam atmosphere eventually condenses to form a liquid water ocean beneath a CO<sub>2</sub>-dominated atmosphere, constraining when Earth first became habitable.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>

<hr />

<h2 id="beyond-earth">Beyond Earth</h2>

<p>The same physics that governed early Earth applies across a wide range of exoplanets. PROTEUS is designed to model any rocky or volatile-rich world, from lava planets orbiting their stars in hours to sub-Neptunes with thick hydrogen envelopes.</p>

<p><strong>Super-Earths</strong> like L 98-59 d (1.6 Earth masses, orbiting an M-dwarf at 0.05 AU) experience intense stellar irradiation and tidal heating from neighbouring planets. These effects can sustain partially molten interiors for billions of years, producing thick outgassed atmospheres that JWST is beginning to characterize. <strong>Lava worlds</strong>, even closer to their host stars, maintain permanent magma oceans with thin silicate atmospheres that glow in thermal emission. <strong>Sub-Neptunes</strong>, the most common planet type in the Galaxy, sit at the boundary between rocky and gaseous worlds: their final atmospheric mass is set by a competition between interior outgassing and XUV-driven escape, both of which PROTEUS tracks self-consistently.</p>

<p>Demonstrations for these scenarios are in preparation. For the underlying science, see our <a href="/publications">publications</a>.</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="what-proteus-computes">What PROTEUS computes</h2>

<p>Each simulation couples multiple physical processes in a single self-consistent calculation: radiative transfer through the atmosphere, convective heat transport in the mantle, thermochemical partitioning of volatiles between melt and gas, stellar evolution, and atmospheric escape. The modules responsible for each process can be swapped independently; see the <a href="/modules">modules page</a> for details.</p>

<p>The outgoing radiation spectra shown in the animation are computed at every time step by the atmosphere module (AGNI), producing synthetic observables that can be compared directly with telescope data from JWST and future missions.</p>

<div class="demo-cta">
  <a href="https://proteus-framework.org/PROTEUS/" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Run PROTEUS yourself</a>
  <a href="https://github.com/FormingWorlds/PROTEUS" class="btn btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Explore the code</a>
</div>

<style is:global>
  .scenario-pane { padding: 0.5rem 0 2rem; }
  .scenario-top { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .scenario-video-col { flex: 7; min-width: 0; }
  .scenario-video-col video {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--pt-line-d);
    border-radius: var(--pt-r-2);
    display: block;
  }
  .scenario-info-col { flex: 5; min-width: 0; }
  .at-a-glance {
    background: var(--pt-basalt);
    border: 1px solid var(--pt-line-d);
    border-radius: var(--pt-r-2);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .at-a-glance h3 {
    font-family: var(--pt-font-mono);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--pt-track-label);
    color: var(--pt-azure);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .at-a-glance table { width: 100%; font-size: 0.9rem; border-collapse: collapse; }
  .at-a-glance td { padding: 0.3rem 0; border: none; vertical-align: top; }
  .at-a-glance td:first-child {
    font-family: var(--pt-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--pt-text-d2);
    padding-right: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 0.42rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .at-a-glance td:last-child { color: var(--pt-text-d); }
  .at-a-glance .outcome {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--pt-line-d);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--pt-text-d2);
  }
  .at-a-glance .outcome strong { color: var(--pt-text-d); }

  .result-gallery { display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .result-card {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    background: var(--pt-basalt);
    border: 1px solid var(--pt-line-d);
    border-radius: var(--pt-r-2);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .result-card img { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .result-card .result-label {
    font-family: var(--pt-font-mono);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--pt-text-d2);
    text-align: center;
  }
  /* Each plot ships in a dark and a light variant; show the one that matches
     the active theme. */
  .result-card .plot-light { display: none; }
  [data-theme="light"] .result-card .plot-dark { display: none; }
  [data-theme="light"] .result-card .plot-light { display: block; }

  .demo-detail { margin-top: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .demo-detail summary {
    color: var(--pt-azure);
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .demo-detail summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .demo-detail summary::before { content: "\25B8\00a0"; }
  .demo-detail[open] summary::before { content: "\25BE\00a0"; }
  .demo-detail .detail-body {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--pt-line-d);
  }
  .demo-detail .detail-body p { font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .demo-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem 0 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--pt-line-d);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .demo-cta .btn { margin: 0.5rem; }

  @media (max-width: 991px) {
    .scenario-top { flex-direction: column; }
    .result-gallery { flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .result-card { flex: 1 1 calc(50% - 0.5rem); }
    .result-card:last-child:nth-child(odd) { flex: 1 1 100%; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 576px) {
    .result-gallery { flex-direction: column; }
    .result-card { flex: 1 1 100%; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  // Honour the OS reduced-motion preference: leave the demo videos paused
  // with their controls instead of autoplaying on a loop.
  if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
      document.querySelectorAll('video[autoplay]').forEach(function (v) {
        v.removeAttribute('autoplay');
        v.removeAttribute('loop');
        v.pause();
      });
    });
  }
</script>
</Base>
